[ctns_demo flashcard]

[ctns_make id='axAssocS1']

    [ctns_backspeak]
Addition and multiplication are associative for a set F if
(x+y)+z = x+(y+z), and if (x * y) * z = x * (y * z) for values x, y, and z in set F.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

    [ctns_front]
Field Axioms - Associativity
    [/ctns_front]
        
    [ctns_back style='font-size:80%;width:70%;']
<strong>Addition and multiplication<br/>are associative</strong> for a set $$\mathbb{F}$$ if<br/>
<br/>$$(x+y)+z = x+(y+z)$$ and<br/><br/>$$(x \cdot y) \cdot z = x \cdot (y \cdot z)$$<br/><br/>for $$x, y, z \in \mathbb{F}.$$<br/>
    [/ctns_back]
    
[/ctns_make]



[ctns_make id='axAssocS2']

    [ctns_backspeak]
Addition is associative for a set F if
(x+y)+z = x+(y+z) for values x-y-and-z in set F.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

    [ctns_front]
Field Axioms<br/><br/>Associativity Under Addition
    [/ctns_front]
        
    [ctns_back]
<strong>Addition is associative</strong><br/>for a set $$\mathbb{F}$$ if
<br/><br/>$$(x+y)+z = x+(y+z)$$ <br/><br/>for $$x, y, z \in \mathbb{F}.$$<br/>
    [/ctns_back]
    
[/ctns_make]


[ctns_make id='axAssocS3']

    [ctns_backspeak]
Multiplication is associative for a set F if
(x times y) times z = x times (y times z) for values x-y-and-z in set F.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

    [ctns_front]
Field Axioms<br/><br/>Associativity Under Multiplication
    [/ctns_front]
        
    [ctns_back]
<strong>Multiplication is associative</strong><br/>for a set $$\mathbb{F}$$ if
<br/><br/>$$(x \cdot y) \cdot z = x \cdot (y \cdot z)$$ <br/><br/>for $$x, y, z \in \mathbb{F}.$$<br/>
    [/ctns_back]
    
[/ctns_make]


[ctns_make id='axClosedS1']

    [ctns_backspeak]
A set F is closed under addition and multiplication if for values x and y in set F, the sum of x plus y and the product of x times y are both unique values, and members of set F.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

    [ctns_front]
Field Axioms - Closure
    [/ctns_front]
        
    [ctns_back style='width:70%;']
A set $$\mathbb{F}$$ is <strong>closed under addition</strong> and <strong>under multiplication</strong> if 
$$x+y \in \mathbb{F}$$ and $$x \cdot y \in \mathbb{F}, $$ and if $$x+y$$ and $$x \cdot y$$ are unique for $$x, y \in \mathbb{F}.$$
    [/ctns_back]
    
[/ctns_make]


[ctns_make id='axClosedS2']

    [ctns_backspeak]
A set F is closed under addition if the sum of x plus y is both unique and a member of F for values x and y in F, 
    [/ctns_backspeak]

    [ctns_front]
Field Axioms<br/><br/>Closure Under Addition
    [/ctns_front]
        
    [ctns_back style='width:70%;']
A set $$\mathbb{F}$$ is <strong>closed under addition</strong> if 
<br/><br/>$$x+y \in \mathbb{F}$$ and $$x+y$$ is unique<br/><br/>for $$x, y \in \mathbb{F}$$.
    [/ctns_back]
    
[/ctns_make]


[ctns_make id='axClosedS3']

    [ctns_backspeak]
A set F is closed under multiplication if the product of x-times-y is unique and a member of F for values x and y in F.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

    [ctns_front]
Field Axioms<br/><br/>Closure Under Multiplication
    [/ctns_front]
        
    [ctns_back style='width:100%;font-size:95%;']
A set $$\mathbb{F}$$ is <strong>closed under multiplication</strong> if<br/><br/>$$x \cdot y \in \mathbb{F}$$ and $$x \cdot y$$ is unique
<br/><br/> for $$x, y \in \mathbb{F}$$.
    [/ctns_back]
    
[/ctns_make]


[ctns_make id='axCommuteS1']

    [ctns_backspeak]
Addition and multiplication are commutative for a set F if
x+y = y+x and if x * y = y * x for values x and y in set F.
    [/ctns_backspeak]
        
    [ctns_front]
Field Axioms - Commutativity
    [/ctns_front]
        
    [ctns_back style='width:70%;font-size:90%;']
<strong>Addition and multiplication are commutative</strong> for a set $$\mathbb{F}$$ if
<br/><br/>$$x+y = y+x$$ &nbsp; and &nbsp; $$x \cdot y = y \cdot x$$<br/><br/>for $$x, y \in \mathbb{F}.$$
    [/ctns_back]
        
[/ctns_make]


