[ctns_make id='axDistS1']

    [ctns_front]
Field Axioms<br/><br/>Multiplication Distributes<br/>Over Addition
    [/ctns_front]
        
    [ctns_backspeak]
Multiplication distributes over addition for a set F if
<br/>x times (y + z) = (x times y) + (x times z)<br/><br/>for values x-y-and-z in F.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

    [ctns_back]
<strong>Multiplication distributes<br/>over addition</strong> for a set $$\mathbb{F}$$ if
<br/><br/>$$x \cdot (y + z) = x \cdot y + x \cdot z$$<br/><br/>for $$x, y, z \in \mathbb{F}.$$
    [/ctns_back]
    
[/ctns_make]


[ctns_make id='axDistS2']

    [ctns_front]
Field Axioms<br/><br/>Addition Distributes<br/>Over Multiplication
    [/ctns_front]
        
    [ctns_backspeak]
Addition distributes<br/>over multiplication for a set F if
<br/>(x + y) times z = (x times z) + (y times z)<br/><br/>for values x-y-and-z in F.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

    [ctns_back]
<strong>Addition distributes over multiplication</strong> for a set $$\mathbb{F}$$ if
<br/><br/>$$(x + y) \cdot z = x \cdot z + y \cdot z$$<br/><br/>for $$x, y, z \in \mathbb{F}.$$
    [/ctns_back]
    
[/ctns_make]


[ctns_make id='axIdentS1']

    [ctns_backspeak]
For a set F and all values of x in F
there is an element 0 in F
x + 0 = x and
there is an element 1 in F
x times 1 = x.
    [/ctns_backspeak]
        
    [ctns_front]
Field Axioms - Identity
    [/ctns_front]
        
    [ctns_back style='font-size:90%;']
For a set $$\mathbb{F}$$ and all $$x \in \mathbb{F},$$<br/><br/>
there is an element $$0 \in \mathbb{F}$$ such that<br/>
$$x + 0 = x,$$ and<br/><br/>
there is an element $$1 \in \mathbb{F}$$ such that<br/>
$$x \cdot 1 = x.$$ 
    [/ctns_back]
    
[/ctns_make]


