[ctns_make id='axInverseS1']

    [ctns_front]
Field Axioms - Inverse
    [/ctns_front]
        
    [ctns_back style='font-size:80%;']
For a set $$\mathbb{F}$$ and all $$x \in \mathbb{F},$$<br/><br/>
there is an element $$-x \in \mathbb{F}$$ such that<br/>
$$x + (-x) = 0,$$<br/><br/>and there is an element $$\frac{1}{x} \in \mathbb{F}$$ such that<br/>
$$x \cdot \left( \frac{1}{x} \right) = 1.$$
    [/ctns_back]
    
[/ctns_make]


[ctns_make id='axInverseS2']

